AUTHOR : Olivier Doorenbos PROJECT STARTED: late 2006 RELEASED: late 2009 (delayed a year due to technical issues etc) MAP DESCRIPTION: A realistic map of a car ferry (as big as the Titanic). Features: - FULL LAYOUT (with a few exceptions) of ALL 11 decks! - 2 VERY ADVANCED LIFTS, fully functional with 9 levels each! - huge moving sea 3D skybox - 40+ custom textures & decals - custom sounds recorded on Maersk Delft - a real car ferry - custom soundscapes - ship can be triggered to gradually sink (drowning everyone) - engine room fires can be triggered & extinguished - 64 spawns with multiple terrorist spawn areas - area specific vibration (most in engine room) - bomb has longer fuse timer as map is big - liftable car deck (can crush), playground (seesaw & carousel) - a radio with music and triggerable ship horn - manually built bot nav mesh LITE VERSION CHANGES: - CT can now buy but don't get extra equipment at start - player movespeed & gravity modifiers removed - most guns found on the ground are removed - reduced filesize by removing both triggerable music tracks, safety announcement, a 6mb texture & the vmf file TECHNICAL STATISTICS: solids/brushes ~ 7500 (near limit set by Source engine) brush faces ~ 48000 point entities ~ 3000 solid entities ~ 800 textures ~ 100 T-junction fixup limit nearly reached (most annoying compile error for this map) COMMENTS: This is the LITE version of the map. It's purpose is to reduce filesize and provide more normal "classic" gameplay. The things that affect gameplay and are not found in normal maps are removed (the built-in speed & gravity mods etc). This is for all the CSS junkies who get very angry when they can't buy their own gun, can't run up a ladder or can't fall 4 meters without getting hurt. So if you want to play this unique map but with normal gameplay, this lite version is for you. I have worked very hard on this for more than a year. Much time and research has gone into making the ship and its layout as realistic as possible - gameplay balance was less important. Most time and work has gone into getting this huge map to compile without critical errors! Please provide constructive criticism and bug reports to help me improve later versions. (If you really want a version with only 1 Terrorist spawn area, just ask and I will make one for you) CREDITS: map, custom textures, most custom sounds & all sound editing by Olivier Doorenbos www.CGTextures.com - source of most raw custom textures dasboot music by Klaus Doldinger ship horn sound from www.youtube.com/BIGMIKESOCAL PRIVILEGES: You can do whatever you want (distribute, edit the VMF file, release modified version etc) as long as you give me credit where it is due and do not profit financially. If you distribute this map, you must include THIS README. The VMF file is not included in this lite version so if you want it (and most of the map's custom resources) for use in your own projects: http://www.filefront.com/14758417/ropax_VMF_resources.zip/

Rooftops is a bomb/defuse map. The plot is about 2 witnesses about to take the stand against a drug cartel. The Cartel plans on eliminating them using c4. Kind of like in "Traffic" when the guy says, "I want to use a bomb. You shoot a guy in the head and they have doctors keeping him alive." So 2 penthouses in the witness protection program are under attack, and it's up to the counter-terrorists to stop the terrorists.

The map features:

2 large bombsites
64 spawn points
VERY tall buildings

I hope you're not afraid of heights!

*note* - When you fall you get teleported back to the top.  You still die, but this makes it to where the bomb will teleport as well, so the T's won't get screwed if the bomber falls.  Not great for realism but great for gameplay.

De_roadhouse_dMw is a remake of the really old cs map de_roadhouse, which is an old favorite of ours. The main layout is the same but some areas have been changed completely. The textures are all new and most of them are custom. The map is set in a roadhouse out in a desert close to nowhere. After an initial firefight the Counter Terrorists have fortified in the roadhouse. The terrorists have regrouped in the mountains and plan a second attack to cause havoc and destruction. There is no drivable car in this version of the map as there is in the old map. Because of this changes have been made to the tunnel to help the T approach to the fuel station. Displacement maps have been used to create a more realistic environment. The Doors Roadhouse Blues is still playing in the restaurant area. We would like to thank the people at Dead Men Walking for testing it. Don't forget to take a look at de_astute_dMw and deagle_crypt_dMw_b3.

This map, de_rio, is a medium-small bomb defuse map for CS:S. The A bomb site is inside a building with a simple layout but many approaches. The B bomb site is on a dock with shallow water underneath. I have a detailed page for this map at my personal website with design notes, annotated screen shots and video of me running around in the map. Let me know if you like it or want to see something get changed. Something I forgot to add is that the map looks like garbage in HDR. I didn't realize my skybox and lighting was all tuned for LDR so I suggest playing it in LDR only.

July 2008 was released one of the most beautiful and cheerful bomb/defuse maps for CS:S! It's worthy to take a place of honor in the same row with such masterpieces of a mapbuilding, as [de_corse](http://css.gamebanana.com/maps/18280) (by Hessi), [de_wellness](http://css.gamebanana.com/maps/81605) (by Maddin), [de_fedra_autumn](http://css.gamebanana.com/maps/151619) (by Wostok) and it is possible still a dozen of others (imho).

"Even if this map is not as beautiful as de_corse, it is one of the nicest CSS maps.
At first sight, the map gameplay is quite usual: large rooms connected by large hallways, with some shortcuts. But this map has more to offer. Here and there, doors are opening to some narrow corridors and rooms. They work the same way as in de_coldhaze or any standard DoDS maps: use them to hide or to ambush.
The gameplay is even better due to some of the mapper's decisions. It may be less realistic (stairs to nowhere?) but it is funnier that way!
A very nice map to discover!" - map review at Netday.be

General Credits and Gratitudes:

An original .nav-file by Man Nay seemed to me imperfect, though was optimized slightly. Well... download, play and enjoy! :-)

Welcome to my first ever map! I've tried to create a balanced, fast paced close quarters defuse  map for counter strike source. The map is based around two main buildings the larger of which links all levels of the map from three storeys above ground to two storeys below ground. Bomb site A is located underground whilst site B can be found on a balcony leading from the top floor office. I have tried to ensure balance and sufficient time to get from one site to another meaning there is always a final face off while the timer is ticking. I have spent a lot of  time tweaking bot navigation to ensure they use the map as intended. There are 12 spawns per side. All areas are named and contain ambient sounds. Please remember this is my first map so be honest to not too harsh with your comments, all feedback will be gratefully received. Hope you enjoy. Rick_0_Shay.
